  "id": "ALSA-2025:8131",
  "summary": "Moderate: ruby security update",
  "details": "Ruby is an extensible, interpreted, object-oriented, scripting language. It has features to process text files and to perform system management tasks.  \n\nSecurity Fix(es):  \n\n  * net-imap: Net::IMAP vulnerable to possible DoS by memory exhaustion (CVE-2025-25186)\n  * CGI: Denial of Service in CGI::Cookie.parse (CVE-2025-27219)\n  * uri: userinfo leakage in URI#join, URI#merge and URI#+ (CVE-2025-27221)\n\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n",
